title: Sweden's ruling center-left in slim election lead, exit poll shows
description: Sweden's center-left bloc looked set for a narrow victory over right-wing opponents, an exit poll showed after voting ended on Sunday, although the anti-immigration Sweden Democrats made gains and could become the second-largest party in parliament.

title: Credit card companies will adopt new sales code for US gun transactions
description: US credit card giants said they will implement a new merchant category code for the nation's gun retailers, which gun control activists say will help flag potential mass shooters and gun traffickers.

title: Antigua and Barbuda to vote on whether to remove British monarch as head of state, PM says
description: The prime minister of Antigua and Barbuda said the Caribbean country will hold a referendum on whether to become a republic and remove King Charles III as the head of state within the next few years.

title: Albania blames Iran for second cyberattack since July
description: Albania blamed the Iranian government Saturday for a cyberattack against computer systems used by Albanian state police — just days after the White House condemned Tehran for a hack that disrupted Albanian government services in July.
